07/03/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Justice Minister Monica Macovei said Friday (4 March) that the government has decided to introduce new, stricter forms of asset disclosures to be submitted by officials. According to Macovei, the declarations would be made public and would include information from spouses. The new forms include seven categories of goods and income subject to declaration.
In other news, President Traian Basescu travels to Washington on Tuesday to meet with US counterpart George W. Bush and other senior officials. He will also talk with representatives of the World Bank and the IMF. (Rompres, Nine o'clock - 07/03/05; Rompres, Nine o'clock - 04/03/05)
